cGgsnSentSigMessages.name: cGgsnSentSigMessages
cGgsnSentSigMessages.description: The number of GTP signalling messages sent.

cGgsnReceivedSigMessages.name: cGgsnReceivedSigMessages
cGgsnReceivedSigMessages.description: The number of GTP signalling messages received.

cGgsnUnexpectedSigMessages.name: cGgsnUnexpectedSigMessages
cGgsnUnexpectedSigMessages.description: The number of unexpected GTP signalling messages received.

cGgsnSentGPDUs.name: cGgsnSentGPDUs
cGgsnSentGPDUs.description: The number of G-PDU messages sent.

cGgsnReceivedGPDUs.name: cGgsnReceivedGPDUs
cGgsnReceivedGPDUs.description: The number of G-PDU messages received.

cGgsnSentGPDUOctets.name: cGgsnSentGPDUOctets
cGgsnSentGPDUOctets.description: The number of total bytes sent in G-PDU messages.

cGgsnReceivedGPDUOctets.name: cGgsnReceivedGPDUOctets
cGgsnReceivedGPDUOctets.description: The number of total bytes received in G-PDU messages.

cGgsnUnexpectedGPDUs.name: cGgsnUnexpectedGPDUs
cGgsnUnexpectedGPDUs.description: The number of unexpected G-PDU messages, for example, non existent PDP contexts and ACL denial.

cGgsnActivationRejectedPdps.name: cGgsnActivationRejectedPdps
cGgsnActivationRejectedPdps.description: The number of PDP contexts that the activation request was rejected.

cGgsnOutOfResourcePdps.name: cGgsnOutOfResourcePdps
cGgsnOutOfResourcePdps.description: The number of PDP contexts that the activation request rejected due to the GGSN running out of resources for transmitting GTP packets. Examples: - Out of memory; - The number of PDPs on GGSN reached limit; - all dynamic PDP address are occupied;

cGgsnParserErrorMessages.name: cGgsnParserErrorMessages
cGgsnParserErrorMessages.description: The number of GTP messages received with wrong value. It includes the following cases: - mandatory and optional information element in the GTP packet is duplicated, missing, unknown, incorrect or out of order. - the GTP message is too short to hold the GTP header for the supported version. - the GTP messages running an unsupported version of GTP. - Unknown GTP message type.

cGgsnTotalCreatedPdps.name: cGgsnTotalCreatedPdps
cGgsnTotalCreatedPdps.description: This object represents the total number of PDP contexts created.

cGgsnTotalDeletedPdps.name: cGgsnTotalDeletedPdps
cGgsnTotalDeletedPdps.description: This object represents the total number of PDP contexts deleted.

cGgsnTotalNetworkInitPdps.name: cGgsnTotalNetworkInitPdps
cGgsnTotalNetworkInitPdps.description: This object represents the total number of PDP contexts activated by the GGSN that were initiated by the PDN.

cGgsnTotalPppPdpsCreated.name: cGgsnTotalPppPdpsCreated
cGgsnTotalPppPdpsCreated.description: This object represents the total number of PPP PDP contexts created.

cGgsnTotalPppPdpsDeleted.name: cGgsnTotalPppPdpsDeleted
cGgsnTotalPppPdpsDeleted.description: This object represents the total number of PPP PDP contexts deleted.

cGgsnOutOfResourcePppRegenPdps.name: cGgsnOutOfResourcePppRegenPdps
cGgsnOutOfResourcePppRegenPdps.description: This object represents the total number of create PDP context and delete PDP context requests rejected due to unavailable resource on the GGSN for PPP regeneration.

cGgsnDroppedPppRegenPdps.name: cGgsnDroppedPppRegenPdps
cGgsnDroppedPppRegenPdps.description: This object represents the total number of create PDP context and delete PDP context requests that were dropped due to the threshold limit being reached for maximum number of PPP regeneration sessions allowed on the GGSN.

cGgsnTftSemanticErrorPdps.name: cGgsnTftSemanticErrorPdps
cGgsnTftSemanticErrorPdps.reference: 3GPP; Technical Specification Group Core Network; General Packet Radio Service(GPRS); GPRS Tunnelling Protocol (GTP) across Gn and Gp Interface (Release 1999). 3G TS 29.060 v3.5.0.
cGgsnTftSemanticErrorPdps.description: This object represents the total number of received PDP context messages that had TFTs with semantic errors.

cGgsnTftSyntacticErrorPdps.name: cGgsnTftSyntacticErrorPdps
cGgsnTftSyntacticErrorPdps.reference: 3GPP; Technical Specification Group Core Network; General Packet Radio Service(GPRS); GPRS Tunnelling Protocol (GTP) across Gn and Gp Interface (Release 1999). 3G TS 29.060 v3.5.0.
cGgsnTftSyntacticErrorPdps.description: This object represents the total number of received PDP context messages that had TFTs with syntactic errors.

cGgsnPktFilterSemanticErrorPdps.name: cGgsnPktFilterSemanticErrorPdps
cGgsnPktFilterSemanticErrorPdps.reference: 3GPP; Technical Specification Group Core Network; General Packet Radio Service(GPRS); GPRS Tunnelling Protocol (GTP) across Gn and Gp Interface (Release 1999). 3G TS 29.060 v3.5.0.
cGgsnPktFilterSemanticErrorPdps.description: This object represents the total number of received PDP context messages that had packet filters with semantic errors.

cGgsnPktFilterSyntacticErrorPdps.name: cGgsnPktFilterSyntacticErrorPdps
cGgsnPktFilterSyntacticErrorPdps.reference: 3GPP; Technical Specification Group Core Network; General Packet Radio Service(GPRS); GPRS Tunnelling Protocol (GTP) across Gn and Gp Interface (Release 1999). 3G TS 29.060 v3.5.0.
cGgsnPktFilterSyntacticErrorPdps.description: This object represents the total number of received PDP context messages that had packet filters with syntactic errors.

cGgsnNotifEnabled.name: cGgsnNotifEnabled
cGgsnNotifEnabled.description: Indicates whether cGgsnNotification notification will be sent when a notification is generated by the device. - 'true', it will enable the device to send a notification, as well as logging the notification to the cGgsnHistNotifTable. - 'false', it will prevent the device from sending out a notification, but it will still log the notification into cGgsnHistNotifTable.

cGgsnNotifLeastSeverLevel.name: cGgsnNotifLeastSeverLevel
cGgsnNotifLeastSeverLevel.description: Indicates the least severity level of the cGgsnNotification notifications to be generated by the device. Thus, notifications are not generated for alarms with a severity level less urgent than the value of this object. This object cannot be set to cleared(1) or indeterminate(2).

cGgsnGeneratedNotifs.name: cGgsnGeneratedNotifs
cGgsnGeneratedNotifs.description: The number of cGgsnNotification notifications that have been generated since sysUpTime.

cGgsnIgnoredAlarms.name: cGgsnIgnoredAlarms
cGgsnIgnoredAlarms.description: The number of alarms which are less severe than cGgsnNotifLeastSeverLevel since sysUpTime, and thus, for which no notification was generated.

cGgsnHistNotifMaxLength.name: cGgsnHistNotifMaxLength
cGgsnHistNotifMaxLength.description: The maximum number of entries to be retained in the cGgsnHistNotifTable. When the table is full, the oldest entries are removed to make space for new entries.

cGgsnHistNotifLatestIndex.name: cGgsnHistNotifLatestIndex
cGgsnHistNotifLatestIndex.description: The value of cGgsnHistNotifIndex for the most recently created entry in cGgsnHistNotifTable.

cGgsnHistNotifTable.name: cGgsnHistNotifTable
cGgsnHistNotifTable.description: A history table of the most recent cGgsnNotification notifications generated by this device. If a new cGgsnNotification notification is generated when the number of entries is equal to cGgsnHistNotifMaxLength, then the oldest entry is deleted and replaced with an entry for the latest notification.

cGgsnHistNotifEntry.name: cGgsnHistNotifEntry
cGgsnHistNotifEntry.description: Detailed information concerning a particular notification that previously generated from this device.

cGgsnHistNotifIndex.name: cGgsnHistNotifIndex
cGgsnHistNotifIndex.description: A monotonically increasing integer for the sole purpose of indexing notifications. When it reaches the maximum value, it wraps the value back to 1.

cGgsnHistNotifType.name: cGgsnHistNotifType
cGgsnHistNotifType.description: This object indicates the type of notification.

cGgsnHistNotifSeverity.name: cGgsnHistNotifSeverity
cGgsnHistNotifSeverity.description: This object indicates the severity level of the notification. This object cannot be set to cleared(1) or indeterminate(2).

cGgsnHistNotifTimestamp.name: cGgsnHistNotifTimestamp
cGgsnHistNotifTimestamp.description: This object indicates the value of sysUpTime when this notification was generated.

cGgsnHistNotifGgsnIpAddrType.name: cGgsnHistNotifGgsnIpAddrType
cGgsnHistNotifGgsnIpAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of Internet address by which cGgsnHistNotifGgsnIpAddr is reachable.

cGgsnHistNotifGgsnIpAddr.name: cGgsnHistNotifGgsnIpAddr
cGgsnHistNotifGgsnIpAddr.description: The object indicates the IP address that uniquely identifies the device which generated the notification.

cGgsnHistNotifInfo.name: cGgsnHistNotifInfo
cGgsnHistNotifInfo.description: A textual description of cGgsnHistNotifType, which potentially contains additional information (more than just the type of alarm). If the text of the message exceeds 64 bytes, the message will be truncated to 63 bytes and a '*' character will be appended to indicate the message has been truncated.

cGgsnDefaultIpAllocationMethod.name: cGgsnDefaultIpAllocationMethod
cGgsnDefaultIpAllocationMethod.description: Specifies the default method by which the GGSN obtains address leases for mobile user sessions. - 'disable', which indicates that dynamic address allocation is disabled. - 'dhcp', which indicates that the DHCP server will be used. - 'radius', which indicates that the radius server will be used.

cGgsnIdlePdpPurgeTimer.name: cGgsnIdlePdpPurgeTimer
cGgsnIdlePdpPurgeTimer.description: This object specifies the time that the GGSN waits before purging idle PDP contexts. A value '0' will disable the purge timer.

cGgsnIpDupProtectTable.name: cGgsnIpDupProtectTable
cGgsnIpDupProtectTable.description: This table contains the range of IP address used in the GPRS PLMN. These IP addresses are used to avoid IP address duplication in GPRS network. IP address duplication occurs when a MS uses an IP address which is already used in the PLMN. The IP addresses configured inside GPRS network should be in these ranges and MS IP address should not be in this range.

cGgsnIpDupProtectEntry.name: cGgsnIpDupProtectEntry
cGgsnIpDupProtectEntry.description: Entry containing the start and end IP address in the address range. An Entry with start IP > end IP is not allowed. No new entry will be accepted if that would cause any IP address(es) to be represented by more than one row in this table.

cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIpType.name: cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIpType
cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIpType.description: The type of Internet address by which cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIp is reachable. The value of this object should be same as cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIpType. Only ipv4(1) addresses are supported.

cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIp.name: cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIp
cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIp.description: Starting IP address in the address range.

cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIpType.name: cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIpType
cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIpType.description: The type of Internet address by which cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIp is reachable. The value of this object should be same as cGgsnMsExcludeRangeStartIpType. Only ipv4(1) addresses are supported.

cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIp.name: cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIp
cGgsnMsExcludeRangeEndIp.description: Ending IP address in the address range.

cGgsnIpDupProtectRowStatus.name: cGgsnIpDupProtectRowStatus
cGgsnIpDupProtectRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or delete an existing row in this table. To create a row, set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row, set this object to 'destroy'.

cGgsnDefaultAggregTable.name: cGgsnDefaultAggregTable
cGgsnDefaultAggregTable.description: This table contains the list of default aggregate routes configured on the GGSN. GGSN uses a static host route to forward user data packets for each PDP context received from Gi interface to Gn interface. Using the aggregate route (address range), the total number of static routes implemented in the GGSN for PDP requests can be greatly reduced.

cGgsnDefaultAggregEntry.name: cGgsnDefaultAggregEntry
cGgsnDefaultAggregEntry.description: An Entry contains the IP network prefix which is used to combine the routes of PDP requests for the same network as a single route on the GGSN.

cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddrType.name: cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddrType
cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddrType.description: This object specifies the type of Internet address denoted by cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddr. Only ipv4(1) addresses are supported.

cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddr.name: cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddr
cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddr.description: This object specifies the IP address whose network prefix is going to be defined by cGgsnDefaultAggregIpMask.

cGgsnDefaultAggregIpMask.name: cGgsnDefaultAggregIpMask
cGgsnDefaultAggregIpMask.description: This object specifies the net-mask pertaining to cGgsnDefaultAggregIpAddr.

cGgsnDefaultAggregRowStatus.name: cGgsnDefaultAggregRowStatus
cGgsnDefaultAggregRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or delete an existing row in this table. To create a row, set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row, set this object to 'destroy'. The values 'createAndWait' and 'notInService' are not supported.

cGgsnDefaultAaaAuthServerGroup.name: cGgsnDefaultAaaAuthServerGroup
cGgsnDefaultAaaAuthServerGroup.description: This object specifies the AAA radius server group that is used for authentication by all APN's on this GGSN.

cGgsnDefaultAaaAccServerGroup.name: cGgsnDefaultAaaAccServerGroup
cGgsnDefaultAaaAccServerGroup.description: This object specifies the AAA radius server group that is used for accounting by all APN's on this GGSN.

cGgsnPppVirtualTemplate.name: cGgsnPppVirtualTemplate
cGgsnPppVirtualTemplate.description: This object represents the virtual template interface used by PPP Type PDP's.

cGgsnPppRegenVirtualTemplate.name: cGgsnPppRegenVirtualTemplate
cGgsnPppRegenVirtualTemplate.description: This object represents the virtual template interface used for PPP Regeneration by the APN's on which PPP Regeneration is configured. The value zero indicates that no interface is specified.

cGgsnPlmnIpAddrRangeTable.name: cGgsnPlmnIpAddrRangeTable
cGgsnPlmnIpAddrRangeTable.description: This table contains the range of IP addresses that belong to the PLMN nodes in a GPRS network. This range does not include address of various entities like RADIUS, DHCP, DNS servers, etc., which are not part of PLMN.

cGgsnPlmnIpAddrRangeEntry.name: cGgsnPlmnIpAddrRangeEntry
cGgsnPlmnIpAddrRangeEntry.description: Entry containing the first and last IP address in the address range. An Entry with first-IP > last-IP is not allowed. No new entry will be accepted if that would cause any IP address(es) to be represented by more than one row in this table.

cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeIpAddrType.name: cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeIpAddrType
cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeIpAddrType.description: The address type for cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeFirstIp and cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeLastIp addresses. Only ipv4(1) addresses are supported.

cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeFirstIp.name: cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeFirstIp
cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeFirstIp.description: First IP address in the address range.

cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeLastIp.name: cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeLastIp
cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeLastIp.description: Last IP address in the address range.

cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeRowStatus.name: cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeRowStatus
cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or delete an existing row in this table. To create a row, set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row, set this object to 'destroy'. To modify a row, the row needs to be deleted and created fresh with new values.

cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeUsage.name: cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeUsage
cGgsnPlmnAddrRangeUsage.description: This object specifies how the address range will be used by the GGSN. When set to 'security', the address range is used for GGSN security feature i.e. any TPDU with destination address that falls in this address range will be discarded. When set to 'sgsn', the address range denotes the sgsn address range in the local PLMN which can be used to check roaming MS.

cGgsnVersion.name: cGgsnVersion
cGgsnVersion.description: This object specifies the which release of GPRS image is currently running on the GGSN.

cGgsnActiveNetworkInitPdps.name: cGgsnActiveNetworkInitPdps
cGgsnActiveNetworkInitPdps.description: This object represents the number of network initiated PDP contexts that are currently active.

cGgsnActivePppPdps.name: cGgsnActivePppPdps
cGgsnActivePppPdps.description: This object represents the number of PPP PDP contexts that are currently active.

cGgsnActivePppRegenPdps.name: cGgsnActivePppRegenPdps
cGgsnActivePppRegenPdps.description: This object represents the number of PPP-Regen PDP contexts that are currently active.

cGgsnPendingPppRegenPdps.name: cGgsnPendingPppRegenPdps
cGgsnPendingPppRegenPdps.description: This object represents the current number of pending PPP regeneration sessions.

cGgsnActiveGtpVersion0Pdps.name: cGgsnActiveGtpVersion0Pdps
cGgsnActiveGtpVersion0Pdps.description: This object represents the current number of active GTP v0 PDP contexts.

cGgsnActiveGtpVersion1Pdps.name: cGgsnActiveGtpVersion1Pdps
cGgsnActiveGtpVersion1Pdps.description: This object represents the current number of active GTP v1 PDP contexts.

cGgsnGtpEncapInterface.name: cGgsnGtpEncapInterface
cGgsnGtpEncapInterface.description: This object represents the ifIndex of the interface on which which gtp encapsulation is configured. Only one interface can be configured with gtp encapsulation on the GGSN. A zero value indicates that no interface is configured with gtp encapsulation.

cGgsnNotification.name: cGgsnNotification
cGgsnNotification.description: This notification indicates the occurrence of a GGSN related alarm. If and when additional useful information is available for specific types of alarms, then that information may be appended to the end of the notification in additional varbinds.
